49:["$","p",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Target (production):"}]," A full distributed key tree — root key, site keys, device keys — where revoking a single site costs O(sites) key update messages, not O(devices). The design principles are identical to v1; the distribution mechanism scales for large deployments. The infrastructure (counter, rotation endpoint, audit log) is already in place."]}]
